# Example: .cursorrules (Cursor IDE)

# Place this content in `.cursor/rules/kernel.mdc` in your project root.
# Or in `.cursorrules` for older Cursor versions.

---
description: Core operating protocols for autonomous development
alwaysApply: true
---

# Agentic Kernel — Cursor Integration

## Primary Directive
Read and follow `.agents/SYSTEM_CORE.md` for all development tasks. Every task must flow through the phase system.

## Workflow Rules

### Planning (Before Writing Code)
- Create a `PLAN.md` with atomic tasks before any implementation
- Each task must have acceptance criteria and dependency ordering
- Mark the first task `[IN PROGRESS]` before coding

### Implementation (While Writing Code)
- Write failing tests FIRST, then implement
- Write ≤50 lines of code between test runs
- If the same approach fails 3 times: STOP, `git reset --hard HEAD && git clean -fd`, and rethink
- Only modify files listed in your scope declaration

### Commits (Before Committing)
- Run the full test suite
- Review your diff across 5 axes: Correctness, Readability, Architecture, Security, Performance
- One task = one commit. Format: `<type>(<scope>): TASK-XXX <description>`

### Memory (After Milestones)
- Update `.docs/architecture/` after structural changes
- Write context snapshots at session boundaries
- Log learnings from failures in `.docs/learned_rules/`

## Hard Constraints
- Never commit failing tests
- Never modify out-of-scope files
- Never batch multiple tasks into one commit
- Never remove code you can't explain (Preserved Intent)
- Always read files before modifying them
- Always use absolute paths when there's ambiguity

## Project Specifics
- Language: [your language]
- Test command: `[your test command]`
- Lint command: `[your lint command]`
